cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about salient object detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a novel framework for this task, which involves constructing partial decoders and refining features of the backbone network. This suggests that the paper may also belong to sub-categories related to machine learning and neural networks, such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed framework on benchmark datasets, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-category of multimedia, cs.MM (Multimedia).
